Bha '''An Rathad Iarruinn Caledonian''' "An Calaidh", na [[Rathad-iarainn|rathad-iarruinn]]  as motha na h- [[Alba]]inn gu ruige 1923 nuair a chaidh e mar "constituent company" do an London Midland and Scottish Railway. 101 miltean 's an fhad, shine bun-loidhne a' Chalaidh bho [[Carlisle]] ( Far an do cheangail e ris an Rathad-Iarruinn "London and North Western") ri Ionad Meadhanach a' [[glaschu|Ghlaschu]]. Bha fior branndair nan rathad-iaruinn an sheilbh a' chompanaidh seo, a chosnaich a' chuid bu mhor den tuarasdail aice bho trachdadh ghuail bho meinichean air feadh Srath Meadhanach na h-Alba. A dh'aindeoin sin, bha a phrìomh gobhalach aig [[Tobar na Mathair]], far an do dhealaich a rathad gu [[Obar Dheathain]]. Thogta fo ainm "The Scottish Central Railway", fhosgladh an meur seo a chaidh tro [[Sruighlea]], [[Peairt|Pheairt]], [[Farfair|Forfair]] agus Ceann Abair gu [[Sròn na h-Aibhne]] agus Obar Dheathain cho trath ri 1848.

